'''Pedro Jeampierre Vite Uca''' (born 9 March 2002) is an Ecuadorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder (association football)|attacking midfielder]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Pumas UNAM|UNAM]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Career==
Vite came up through the youth system at [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]], going on to help the team win the [[U-20 Copa Libertadores]] in 2020.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/whitecaps-fc-acquire-19-year-old-ecuadorian-attacking-midfielder-pedro-vite|title=Whitecaps FC acquire 19-year-old Ecuadorian attacking midfielder Pedro Vite &#124; Vancouver Whitecaps|website=whitecapsfc}}</ref> He made his professional debut for Independiente's reserve team, [[C.D. Independiente Juniors|Independiente Juniors]], in 2019 in the [[Ecuadorian Serie B]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.benditofutbol.com/nacional/independiente-valle-despidio-pedro-vite.html|title=Independiente del Valle se despidió de Pedro Vite y William Pacho|website=Bendito Futbol|access-date=2021-08-30|archive-date=2023-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230419121117/https://www.benditofutbol.com/nacional/independiente-valle-despidio-pedro-vite.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2021, Vite played his first season in the [[Ecuadorian Serie A]], scoring two goals and tallying four assists in 14 appearances. He also played one match in the [[Supercopa Ecuador]], and made ten appearances in the [[Copa Libertadores]], scoring one goal and registering two assists across the tournament.<ref name="auto"/>

On 5 August 2021, Vite signed with [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]].<ref name="auto"/>

